Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.75,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“哎呀，真是感谢工业社会拯救了咱，让我们免于此等水深火热”
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.75,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Thank you, Industrial Society, for saving us from this, 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:03.75,0:00:09.68,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,某条网帖配着瑞士阿尔卑斯山如画美景，反讽地写道
Dialogue: 1,0:00:03.75,0:00:09.68,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,sarcastically declares one internet post, featuring a picturesque view of the Swiss Alps.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:09.68,0:00:12.82,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,以前呐，单靠一个爷们儿的收入，就能养得起郊区的房子
Dialogue: 1,0:00:09.68,0:00:12.82,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Can you believe people used to afford a suburban home, 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:12.82,0:00:17.68,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,车子、三个娃子，还能度假、上大学，你敢信？
Dialogue: 1,0:00:12.82,0:00:17.68,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,a car, three kids, a holiday, and college, all on the income of one guy?
Dialogue: 2,0:00:17.68,0:00:19.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,如今这世道是怎么了？
Dialogue: 1,0:00:17.68,0:00:19.72,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,What happened to society? 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:19.72,0:00:21.61,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,怀旧党们不禁扼腕叹息
Dialogue: 1,0:00:19.72,0:00:21.61,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,asks the nostalgics.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:21.61,0:00:27.31,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“拒绝现代，拥抱传统”——密苏里州一位16岁的小年轻
Dialogue: 1,0:00:21.61,0:00:27.31,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Reject modernity. Embrace tradition, says the 16-year-old teenager in Missouri, 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:27.31,0:00:31.02,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,发了张俩人站在电线杆前的照片，并如是说道
Dialogue: 1,0:00:27.31,0:00:31.02,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,posting a picture of two people standing in front of a power line.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:31.02,0:00:35.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“中世纪的农民啊，那闲暇时间和假期可比今天的人多多了”
Dialogue: 1,0:00:31.02,0:00:35.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Medieval peasants had more free time and holidays than people today, 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:35.12,0:00:40.16,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,另一则高论获得了足足11万7千个赞
Dialogue: 1,0:00:35.12,0:00:40.16,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,proclaims another, to over 117,000 likes.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:40.16,0:00:43.80,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,嘿，哥们儿，当今世上还有几十亿人
Dialogue: 1,0:00:40.16,0:00:43.80,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Hey pal, there are billions of people in the world today 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:43.80,0:00:49.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,过着中世纪农民般的日子呢，他们的工时显然可没比咱们少
Dialogue: 1,0:00:43.80,0:00:49.72,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,who live the lives of medieval peasants, and they clearly don't work fewer hours than we do.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:49.72,0:00:53.80,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这类论调啊，可谓是当代数字“时代精神”的缩影
Dialogue: 1,0:00:49.72,0:00:53.80,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This kind of talking point is part of today's digital zeitgeist,
Dialogue: 2,0:00:53.80,0:00:57.06,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,横跨了各种立场和年龄段
Dialogue: 1,0:00:53.80,0:00:57.06,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,from across a spectrum of viewpoints and age groups.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:57.06,0:00:58.90,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当然，我知道不是所有人都这么想
Dialogue: 1,0:00:57.06,0:00:58.90,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And I know it's not all people, 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:58.90,0:01:01.80,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,大多数人心里清楚，咱这日子是前所未有的好
Dialogue: 1,0:00:58.90,0:01:01.80,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,most people know we've never had it so good.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:01.80,0:01:07.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,本视频专供那些真心实意认为“今不如昔”的朋友们“享用”
Dialogue: 1,0:01:01.80,0:01:07.92,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This video is for the folks who genuinely believe that life was better in the good old days.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:07.92,0:01:10.44,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,那会儿啊，更幸福，更淳朴
Dialogue: 1,0:01:07.92,0:01:10.44,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Happier, more virtuous.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:10.44,0:01:15.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,虽说没那么多花里胡哨的好玩意儿，但一切都那么有条不紊
Dialogue: 1,0:01:10.44,0:01:15.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,We didn't have as many nice things, but everything made sense.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:15.12,0:01:17.94,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,无论是衣着、建筑、还是社交礼仪
Dialogue: 1,0:01:15.12,0:01:17.94,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The outfits, the buildings, the social queues, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:17.94,0:01:24.15,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,人们比现在友善多了，也更虔诚，更受人尊敬
Dialogue: 1,0:01:17.94,0:01:24.15,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,people being more friendly than they used to, people being more religious, more public esteem.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:24.15,0:01:26.15,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们的终极结论可能是
Dialogue: 1,0:01:24.15,0:01:26.15,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Ultimately, they might say, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:26.15,0:01:31.65,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们必须回归传统，回归那种相夫教子的保守生活
Dialogue: 1,0:01:26.15,0:01:31.65,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,we must return to tradition, and a domestic, conservative way of living.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:32.42,0:01:37.16,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而我，只用一句话就能把这些怼回去：你想过那种日子，谁拦着你了？
Dialogue: 1,0:01:32.42,0:01:37.16,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And I can easily dismiss all of that as bullshit by saying, you can already do that.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:37.16,0:01:42.00,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,你大可以去过田园牧歌的农耕生活，假装自己是个中世纪老农
Dialogue: 1,0:01:37.16,0:01:42.00,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,You can go and live a pastoral farmsteading life and pretend you're a medieval peasant.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:42.00,0:01:43.21,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,毕竟这也不犯法
Dialogue: 1,0:01:42.00,0:01:43.21,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It's not illegal.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:43.21,0:01:48.13,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当今社会，就有不少人过着仿佛1950年代，乃至1880年代的生活
Dialogue: 1,0:01:43.21,0:01:48.13,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,There are many people today who live as if it was the 1950s or the 1880s.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:48.13,0:01:50.77,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,你根本不用昭告天下
Dialogue: 1,0:01:48.13,0:01:50.77,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,You don't have to advertise it to the world.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:50.77,0:01:54.70,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,你和阿米什人的区别在于，人家是真刀真枪地在践行
Dialogue: 1,0:01:50.77,0:01:54.70,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,What separates you from the Amish is that they're actually devoted.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:54.70,0:01:58.25,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们是真正在过着你声称想要的生活
Dialogue: 1,0:01:54.70,0:01:58.25,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They actually live the life that you purport to want.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:58.25,0:02:02.70,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而当他们被要求解释那个逝去的年代究竟好在哪儿时
Dialogue: 1,0:01:58.25,0:02:02.70,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And when they get asked to explain what made this bygone era so great, 
Dialogue: 2,0:02:02.70,0:02:05.37,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,答案总是围绕着人们“没有”什么
Dialogue: 1,0:02:02.70,0:02:05.37,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,it's always about what people didn't have.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:05.37,0:02:08.70,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,仿佛日子就是因为“更糟”才“更好”的
Dialogue: 1,0:02:05.37,0:02:08.70,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,As if things were better because they were worse.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:08.70,0:02:10.70,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,哦，我们那时候没有智能手机
Dialogue: 1,0:02:08.70,0:02:10.70,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Oh, we didn't always have smartphones.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:10.70,0:02:12.37,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们必须和彼此交谈
Dialogue: 1,0:02:10.70,0:02:12.37,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,We had to talk to each other.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:12.37,0:02:14.18,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们没有中央供暖
Dialogue: 1,0:02:12.37,0:02:14.18,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,We didn't have central heating.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:14.18,0:02:16.16,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但我们因此更快乐
Dialogue: 1,0:02:14.18,0:02:16.16,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And we were happier for it.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:16.16,0:02:18.19,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不，你他喵的才不快乐
Dialogue: 1,0:02:16.16,0:02:18.19,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,No, you fucking weren't.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:18.19,0:02:22.67,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,50年代的时候，不到一半的英国家庭有浴室
Dialogue: 1,0:02:18.19,0:02:22.67,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Back in the 50s, less than half of British households had a bathroom.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:22.67,0:02:24.70,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,人们对此深恶痛绝
Dialogue: 1,0:02:22.67,0:02:24.70,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And people hated it.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:24.70,0:02:27.75,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,有家报纸说，在一个文明国家
Dialogue: 1,0:02:24.70,0:02:27.75,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,With one newspaper saying it was disconcerting 
Dialogue: 2,0:02:27.75,0:02:34.48,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,竟有如此多的人只能靠便携式浴盆洗澡，真是闹斯特麻麻了
Dialogue: 1,0:02:27.75,0:02:34.48,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,that so many people in a civilised country were stuck with the bleak alternative of a portable bath.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:34.48,0:02:37.31,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,大多数房子甚至没有室内厕所
Dialogue: 1,0:02:34.48,0:02:37.31,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Most houses didn't even have an indoor toilet.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:37.31,0:02:40.22,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,厕所远在花园尽头的小棚子里
Dialogue: 1,0:02:37.31,0:02:40.22,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It was in the shed at the bottom of the garden.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:40.22,0:02:45.78,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,许多人回望那个时代，视其为社会高度统一和家庭价值观的黄金年代
Dialogue: 1,0:02:40.22,0:02:45.78,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Many people look back on this time as a golden age of social conformity and family values.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:45.78,0:02:51.20,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,后来“大逆不道”的性、世俗和艺术革命毁掉了他们珍视的一切
Dialogue: 1,0:02:45.78,0:02:51.20,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Before the sexual, secular, artistic revolution ruined everything that was important to them.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:51.20,0:02:58.55,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,另一些人则将其视为“正经工作”的顶峰，工业、高薪、且稳定的高薪
Dialogue: 1,0:02:51.20,0:02:58.55,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Others look back on it as the high point of real proper jobs, in industry, high wages, secure wages.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:58.55,0:03:00.08,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而且还有工会罩着
Dialogue: 1,0:02:58.55,0:03:00.08,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And they were unionised.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:00.08,0:03:04.03,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,贫富差距达到了历史上的最小点
Dialogue: 1,0:03:00.08,0:03:04.03,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Wealth disparities were at its smallest ever in history.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:04.03,0:03:06.97,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,有时，这种怀旧甚至无关政治
Dialogue: 1,0:03:04.03,0:03:06.97,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And sometimes it isn't even political.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:06.97,0:03:10.10,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,Facebook上充斥着无数的老登群组
Dialogue: 1,0:03:06.97,0:03:10.10,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,There are countless Facebook groups full of older generations 
Dialogue: 2,0:03:10.10,0:03:14.16,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,纪念着上世纪中叶那些平平无奇的琐碎事物
Dialogue: 1,0:03:10.10,0:03:14.16,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,commemorating many of the banal complexities of the mid-century.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:14.16,0:03:17.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,从老式转盘电话到垃圾工
Dialogue: 1,0:03:14.16,0:03:17.72,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Everything from rotary phones to bin men.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:17.72,0:03:20.64,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,哎我真是曹乐，他们竟然连垃圾工都要搞政治正确
Dialogue: 1,0:03:17.72,0:03:20.64,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Oh, goddammit, they made the bin men woke.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:20.90,0:03:24.07,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然而，多亏了神奇的历史档案
Dialogue: 1,0:03:20.90,0:03:24.07,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,However, thanks to the wonders of historical archives, 
Dialogue: 2,0:03:24.07,0:03:28.01,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们得以描绘出一幅1950年代的真实生活画卷
Dialogue: 1,0:03:24.07,0:03:28.01,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,we can paint an accurate picture of normal life in the 1950s,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:28.01,0:03:32.65,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,一幅未经怀旧滤镜和流行文化扭曲的画卷
Dialogue: 1,0:03:28.01,0:03:32.65,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,untainted by nostalgia and distortion by popular culture.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:36.71,0:03:37.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,住房
Dialogue: 1,0:03:36.71,0:03:37.54,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Houses.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:37.54,0:03:44.21,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,没人想住鸽子笼，但1950年代的房子，面积还不到今天房子的一半大
Dialogue: 1,0:03:37.54,0:03:44.21,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Nobody wants to live in a pod, but houses in the 1950s were less than half as big as houses of today.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:44.21,0:03:46.43,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,看看这个“豪华住宅”的广告
Dialogue: 1,0:03:44.21,0:03:46.43,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Look at this ad for a luxury home.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:46.43,0:03:49.89,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,按今天的标准来看，也就平平无奇，甚至可以说相当局促
Dialogue: 1,0:03:46.43,0:03:49.89,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It's pretty average or even quite cramped by today's standards.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:49.89,0:03:54.37,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,虽然那会儿房价肯定更便宜，但你可别想着装修
Dialogue: 1,0:03:49.89,0:03:54.37,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And while it was certainly cheaper, don't even think about renovating it.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:54.37,0:03:57.52,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,有些房子的浴室墙壁里有特制的空槽
Dialogue: 1,0:03:54.37,0:03:57.52,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Some houses were built with special caverns in the bathroom walls 
Dialogue: 2,0:03:57.52,0:04:01.67,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,你用完的剃须刀片就直接扔进去，然后抛诸脑后
Dialogue: 1,0:03:57.52,0:04:01.67,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,where you would simply dump all your used razors and then forget about them,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:01.67,0:04:05.15,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,把这一堆生锈的刀片留给下一个倒霉蛋去处理
Dialogue: 1,0:04:01.67,0:04:05.15,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,leaving the next person to deal with all those rusty blades.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:05.47,0:04:09.03,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,如果你想砸开那堵墙，我希望你先打好破伤风疫苗
Dialogue: 1,0:04:05.47,0:04:09.03,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,If you want to knock down that wall, I hope you have your tetanus vaccine.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:09.03,0:04:12.26,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这还是在你买得起“豪华”私宅的前提下
Dialogue: 1,0:04:09.03,0:04:12.26,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,That's even if you could afford the luxury of your own home.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:12.26,0:04:16.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,那时的白人贫困率是现在的两倍，至于黑人贫困率嘛……
Dialogue: 1,0:04:12.26,0:04:16.54,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The white poverty rate was double back then, and the black poverty rate...
Dialogue: 2,0:04:16.54,0:04:17.96,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,你懂的
Dialogue: 1,0:04:16.54,0:04:17.96,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,well, you can already guess.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:17.96,0:04:19.08,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,汽车
Dialogue: 1,0:04:17.96,0:04:19.08,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Cars.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:19.08,0:04:21.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当时的汽车简直是移动棺材
Dialogue: 1,0:04:19.08,0:04:21.60,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Cars at the time were death traps.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:21.60,0:04:23.99,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,人们对汽车物理学一知半解
Dialogue: 1,0:04:21.60,0:04:23.99,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Cars physics were not well understood.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:23.99,0:04:28.32,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们天真地以为，只要不断给车增加厚度，车就能“吸收”掉碰撞
Dialogue: 1,0:04:23.99,0:04:28.32,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They thought if you keep adding bulk to it, the car will just absorb the crash.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:28.32,0:04:34.01,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,结果呢，只是把所有的冲击力，原封不动地转移到了车内脆弱的“肉馅”上
Dialogue: 1,0:04:28.32,0:04:34.01,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Instead, it just transferred all the impact force into the frail meat puppets inside.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:34.52,0:04:35.38,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,城市
Dialogue: 1,0:04:34.52,0:04:35.38,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Cities.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:35.38,0:04:41.71,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,直到1970年代环保运动兴起，在街上乱扔垃圾才被视为一种社会禁忌
Dialogue: 1,0:04:35.38,0:04:41.71,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Littering in the street wasn't seen as socially taboo until the 1970s environmentalist movement.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:41.71,0:04:46.97,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,那时可没有什么空气污染管制，工厂玩命地喷着煤灰和烟尘
Dialogue: 1,0:04:41.71,0:04:46.97,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,There were no regulations on air pollution, so factories spewed out as much coal and smoke dust
Dialogue: 2,0:04:46.97,0:04:51.37,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,像匹兹堡这样的重工业城镇，那是经常不见天日
Dialogue: 1,0:04:46.97,0:04:51.37,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,that it often blocked out the sun in highly industrial towns like Pittsburgh.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:51.37,0:04:56.02,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,又比如伦敦，仅1952年12月的短短四天里
Dialogue: 1,0:04:51.37,0:04:56.02,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Or in London, where over just four days in December 1952, 
Dialogue: 2,0:04:56.02,0:04:59.00,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,大烟雾就夺走了约12000人的生命
Dialogue: 1,0:04:56.02,0:04:59.00,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,smog killed roughly 12,000 people,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:59.00,0:05:01.82,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,并导致10万人严重患病
Dialogue: 1,0:04:59.00,0:05:01.82,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and made 100,000 seriously ill.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:01.82,0:05:04.59,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不过，我得给怀旧党们扳回一城
Dialogue: 1,0:05:01.82,0:05:04.59,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I will give the nostalgists one victory, though.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:04.59,0:05:09.77,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,与今天相比，1950年代的盗窃率和入室盗窃率确实低得惊人
Dialogue: 1,0:05:04.59,0:05:09.77,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Theft and burglary rates were incredibly low in the 1950s compared to today.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:09.77,0:05:14.23,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,虽然这大概是因为大家都没啥值得偷的东西吧（笑）
Dialogue: 1,0:05:09.77,0:05:14.23,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Although, that's because nobody had anything worth stealing.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:14.60,0:05:15.48,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,工作
Dialogue: 1,0:05:14.60,0:05:15.48,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Work.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:15.48,0:05:20.99,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,美国男性平均每年要比现在多工作约300个小时
Dialogue: 1,0:05:15.48,0:05:20.99,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The average American man worked about 300 more hours per year than today.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:20.99,0:05:24.50,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而且吭哧吭哧干了半天，也没多拿几个子儿
Dialogue: 1,0:05:20.99,0:05:24.50,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And he didn't even get paid more for all this toil.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:24.50,0:05:30.93,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,剔除通胀因素后，1957年的工资中位数，甚至略低于今天
Dialogue: 1,0:05:24.50,0:05:30.93,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Adjusting for inflation, the median salary in 1957 was slightly lower than it is today.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:30.93,0:05:36.00,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他得7点半才到家，回家揍完老婆就径直上床睡觉了
Dialogue: 1,0:05:30.93,0:05:36.00,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,He isn't getting home until 7:30, and he's going straight to bed after beating his wife.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:36.00,0:05:41.13,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,至于那个“在家貌美如花、在外温顺听话”的妻子形象，也纯属扯淡
Dialogue: 1,0:05:36.00,0:05:41.13,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The idea of a gorgeous, stay-at-home, submissive wife is a load of nonsense, too.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:41.13,0:05:46.18,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,三分之一的已婚妇女仍然有工作，诚然，这比例是今天的一半
Dialogue: 1,0:05:41.13,0:05:46.18,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,One in three married women still had jobs, which is half the rate it is today, true,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:46.18,0:05:49.01,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但也绝对是女性中不小的一部分了
Dialogue: 1,0:05:46.18,0:05:49.01,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,but it's certainly a large chunk of women.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:49.01,0:05:54.78,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而那些被迫沦为家庭主妇的女性，往往觉得这种生活既无聊又空虚
Dialogue: 1,0:05:49.01,0:05:54.78,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Women who were relegated to being housewives often found it boring and unfulfilling.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:54.78,0:05:57.53,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我问自己，为何如此不满
Dialogue: 1,0:05:54.78,0:05:57.53,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I ask myself why I'm so dissatisfied.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:57.53,0:06:02.61,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我身体健康，孩子可爱，有漂亮的新家，钱也够用
Dialogue: 1,0:05:57.53,0:06:02.61,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I've got my health, fine children, a lovely new home, enough money.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:02.61,0:06:06.17,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我丈夫作为电子工程师，前途一片光明
Dialogue: 1,0:06:02.61,0:06:06.17,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,My husband has a real future as an electronics engineer.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:06.17,0:06:08.34,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他可没有我这些破感受
Dialogue: 1,0:06:06.17,0:06:08.34,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,He doesn't have any of these feelings.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:08.34,0:06:11.16,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我一觉醒来，对生活毫无期待
Dialogue: 1,0:06:08.34,0:06:11.16,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I wake up and there's nothing to look forward to.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:11.16,0:06:13.66,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我试过了所有女人应该做的事
Dialogue: 1,0:06:11.16,0:06:13.66,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I've tried everything women are supposed to do.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:13.66,0:06:17.13,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,培养爱好、侍弄花园、和邻居们打成一片
Dialogue: 1,0:06:13.66,0:06:17.13,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Hobbies, gardening, being very social with my neighbors.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:17.13,0:06:19.89,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我开始觉得自己毫无个性
Dialogue: 1,0:06:17.13,0:06:19.89,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I begin to feel I have no personality.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:19.89,0:06:22.64,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我只是个召之即来，挥之即去的工具人
Dialogue: 1,0:06:19.89,0:06:22.64,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I'm somebody who can be called on when you want something.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:22.64,0:06:23.85,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但我到底是谁
Dialogue: 1,0:06:22.64,0:06:23.85,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But who am I?
Dialogue: 2,0:06:23.85,0:06:25.90,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我好像总是在睡觉
Dialogue: 1,0:06:23.85,0:06:25.90,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I seem to sleep so much.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:25.90,0:06:28.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我不知道自己为什么总是这么累
Dialogue: 1,0:06:25.90,0:06:28.54,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I don't know why I should be so tired.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:28.54,0:06:30.08,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,并不是因为干了多少活
Dialogue: 1,0:06:28.54,0:06:30.08,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It's not the work.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:30.08,0:06:32.26,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我只觉得，我根本没有在“活着”
Dialogue: 1,0:06:30.08,0:06:32.26,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I just don't feel alive.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:35.30,0:06:38.36,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当然，也并非每个人都虔诚又纯洁
Dialogue: 1,0:06:35.30,0:06:38.36,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Nor was everybody pious and morally pure.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:38.36,0:06:43.84,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,早在1939年，只有少数英国人相信有来生
Dialogue: 1,0:06:38.36,0:06:43.84,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,As early as 1939, a minority of Britons believed in life after death,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:43.84,0:06:48.16,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这表明，那时的人们可能并不像我们想象的那么宗教化
Dialogue: 1,0:06:43.84,0:06:48.16,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,indicating that maybe people back then weren't as religious as we think.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:48.45,0:06:52.49,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,1950年代的电影总给人一种印象，好像每个人都是品行端正
Dialogue: 1,0:06:48.45,0:06:52.49,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,1950s cinema gives the impression that everyone acted as upstanding
Dialogue: 2,0:06:52.49,0:06:55.43,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不近女色、满口雅言的模范公民
Dialogue: 1,0:06:52.49,0:06:55.43,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,sexless, clean-mouthed citizens all the time.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:55.43,0:06:59.30,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但这不过是那些大制片厂的“行业自律”罢了
Dialogue: 1,0:06:55.43,0:06:59.30,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But that was just voluntary regulation by the big studios.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:59.30,0:07:03.39,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这边是富丽堂皇的电影院，放着毫无“性”趣的好莱坞浪漫剧
Dialogue: 1,0:06:59.30,0:07:03.39,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,For every grand cinema showing the latest Hollywood romance devoid of sex,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:03.39,0:07:09.08,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,那边就有更多乌烟瘴气的苍蝇馆子，放着低成本、很攒劲的色情片
Dialogue: 1,0:07:03.39,0:07:09.08,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,there were many more seedy dive cinemas showing low-budget, raunchy sexploitation movies.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:09.08,0:07:14.44,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,伦敦的苏豪区，当年可是以成人影院和脱衣舞俱乐部闻名全球的
Dialogue: 1,0:07:09.08,0:07:14.44,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Soho in London was internationally famous for its adult theatres and strip clubs.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:14.44,0:07:17.47,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,备受争议的性学研究者阿尔弗雷德·金赛
Dialogue: 1,0:07:14.44,0:07:17.47,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Alfred Kinsey, a controversial sex researcher, 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.44,0:07:17.47,Yahei-1920x1080,atg3,0,0,0,,他把和他共事的人也干了，不限男女
Dialogue: 2,0:07:17.47,0:07:20.74,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在1953年发现，大约一半的白人女性
Dialogue: 1,0:07:17.47,0:07:20.74,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,found in 1953 that around half of white women
Dialogue: 2,0:07:20.74,0:07:27.32,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,和68%的大学白人男学生，在美利坚有过婚前性行为
Dialogue: 1,0:07:20.74,0:07:27.32,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and 68% of college student white men in America had engaged in premarital intercourse.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:27.68,0:07:30.04,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,至于说脏话，也相当普遍
Dialogue: 1,0:07:27.68,0:07:30.04,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Swearing, also pretty common.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:30.04,0:07:34.37,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这儿有一些好莱坞老电影的NG片段，全是演员忘词儿的
Dialogue: 1,0:07:30.04,0:07:34.37,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Here's some outtakes from old Hollywood films where the actors mess up their lines.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:34.37,0:08:06.20,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,自己练听力吧
Dialogue: 2,0:08:06.20,0:08:09.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这还只是混迹职场的大牌女演员
Dialogue: 1,0:08:06.20,0:08:09.72,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And that's just the high-profile actresses who were in the workplace.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:12.47,0:08:18.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,你大可以想象一下，在日常闲聊中，普罗大众会飙出什么样的脏话
Dialogue: 1,0:08:12.47,0:08:18.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,You can imagine the kind of foul-mouthed language used by everyday people in casual settings.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:19.02,0:08:22.87,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,听完这些，怀旧党们可能得把目光放得更远了
Dialogue: 1,0:08:19.02,0:08:22.87,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Having heard all this, the nostalgic may look back even further.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:22.87,0:08:25.95,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,如果1950年代并不如我想的那么保守
Dialogue: 1,0:08:22.87,0:08:25.95,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,If the 1950s weren't as conservative as I thought, 
Dialogue: 2,0:08:25.95,0:08:29.22,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,那，真正的“美好旧时光”一定是在1920年代
Dialogue: 1,0:08:25.95,0:08:29.22,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,well, the true good old days must have been the 1920s, 
Dialogue: 2,0:08:29.22,0:08:31.99,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,或者1800年代，再或是中世纪
Dialogue: 1,0:08:29.22,0:08:31.99,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,or the 1800s, the Middle Ages. 
Dialogue: 2,0:08:31.99,0:08:33.97,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但这纯粹是一场比惨大赛
Dialogue: 1,0:08:31.99,0:08:33.97,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But it's all a race to the bottom, 
Dialogue: 2,0:08:33.97,0:08:37.57,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,因为保守派们总是在念叨着
Dialogue: 1,0:08:33.97,0:08:37.57,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,because conservatives have always been talking about
Dialogue: 2,0:08:37.57,0:08:39.01,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“美好的旧时光”
Dialogue: 1,0:08:37.57,0:08:39.01,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the good old days.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:39.01,0:08:42.10,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在1930年代，一家英国报纸报道称
Dialogue: 1,0:08:39.01,0:08:42.10,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,In the 1930s, one English newspaper reported,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:42.10,0:08:46.81,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“在历史上，没有任何一个时期的年轻人，曾如此旗帜鲜明地
Dialogue: 1,0:08:42.10,0:08:46.81,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,There is no period in history in which young people have given such emphatic utterance
Dialogue: 2,0:08:46.81,0:08:51.47,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,表现出一种抛弃旧事物、渴望新事物的倾向”
Dialogue: 1,0:08:46.81,0:08:51.47,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,to a tendency to project that which is old and wish for that which is new.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:51.47,0:08:56.82,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,另一家报纸则指责道，“父母们自己，常常未能尽到他们最基本的责任
Dialogue: 1,0:08:51.47,0:08:56.82,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,With another blaming, parents themselves having frequently failed in their obvious duty to
Dialogue: 2,0:08:56.82,0:09:00.85,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,即教会自己的孩子自控和纪律”
Dialogue: 1,0:08:56.82,0:09:00.85,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,teach self-control and discipline to their own children.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:01.20,0:09:07.89,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,1939年，一项盖洛普民调显示，高达62%的美国人认为
Dialogue: 1,0:09:01.20,0:09:07.89,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,In 1939, a Gallup poll revealed that 62% of Americans thought that life was better 
Dialogue: 2,0:09:07.89,0:09:10.63,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,那个“马车时代”的生活更胜一筹
Dialogue: 1,0:09:07.89,0:09:10.63,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,in the era of horse and boogie. 
Dialogue: 2,0:09:11.09,0:09:15.99,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,1890年代的美国，其生活水平堪比当代的马拉维
Dialogue: 1,0:09:11.09,0:09:15.99,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,America in the 1890s had a standard of living comparable to modern day Malawi, 
Dialogue: 2,0:09:15.99,0:09:18.56,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,也就是这世界上最穷的国家
Dialogue: 1,0:09:15.99,0:09:18.56,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the poorest country in the world. 
Dialogue: 2,0:09:18.56,0:09:24.25,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,20世纪初，美国和英国的人均预期寿命约为52岁
Dialogue: 1,0:09:18.56,0:09:24.25,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Life expectancy at the turn of the 20th century was around 52 in the US and UK, 
Dialogue: 2,0:09:24.25,0:09:26.49,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,欧洲大陆那边还要再低一点
Dialogue: 1,0:09:24.25,0:09:26.49,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and a bit lower on the continent. 
Dialogue: 2,0:09:26.49,0:09:31.45,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,放眼当今世界，只有两个国家的预期寿命有这么低
Dialogue: 1,0:09:26.49,0:09:31.45,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,There are only two countries in the world today with a life expectancy that low.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:31.45,0:09:33.69,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,尼日利亚和乍得
Dialogue: 1,0:09:31.45,0:09:33.69,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Nigeria and Chad.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:33.69,0:09:38.05,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但显然，就连这种日子，对于19世纪的人来说都太“安逸”了
Dialogue: 1,0:09:33.69,0:09:38.05,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But apparently even this was too cushy for people in the 19th century.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:38.05,0:09:42.25,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,1832年，安德鲁·杰克逊宣称，在他的领导下
Dialogue: 1,0:09:38.05,0:09:42.25,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,In 1832, Andrew Jackson proclaimed that under his leadership, 
Dialogue: 2,0:09:42.25,0:09:47.94,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,合众国正在“复兴那种忠贞的爱国主义和妥协精神
Dialogue: 1,0:09:42.25,0:09:47.94,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the United States was Reviving that devoted patriotism and spirit of compromise
Dialogue: 2,0:09:47.94,0:09:52.78,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这正是大革命先贤们和我们联邦之父的卓越品质”
Dialogue: 1,0:09:47.94,0:09:52.78,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,which distinguished the sages of the revolution and the fathers of our union. 
Dialogue: 2,0:09:52.78,0:09:59.96,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,显然，50年前，也就是1770年代，那个18世纪，日子要更好
Dialogue: 1,0:09:52.78,0:09:59.96,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Evidently, things were better 50 years ago, in the 1770s, the 18th century.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:59.96,0:10:03.56,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但即便是在18世纪，人们也在抱怨
Dialogue: 1,0:09:59.96,0:10:03.56,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But even in the 18th century, people complained that 
Dialogue: 2,0:10:03.56,0:10:07.40,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,说那些年轻的贵族，公然违背良善品德 
Dialogue: 1,0:10:03.56,0:10:07.40,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,young noblemen who, in direct opposition to good character, 
Dialogue: 2,0:10:07.40,0:10:11.75,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,终日沉溺于纸醉金迷、放荡不羁的生活
Dialogue: 1,0:10:07.40,0:10:11.75,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,hurry through life in one invariable round of debauchery. 
Dialogue: 2,0:10:11.75,0:10:15.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,最后总结道，这些年轻人虽然业已成年
Dialogue: 1,0:10:11.75,0:10:15.60,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Ultimately saying that, despite having attained maturity, 
Dialogue: 2,0:10:15.60,0:10:19.46,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,却一个个骨瘦如柴
Dialogue: 1,0:10:15.60,0:10:19.46,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,young men are naught but emaciated.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:19.46,0:10:23.07,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我的意思是，瞧瞧这家伙，他居然穿长筒袜
Dialogue: 1,0:10:19.46,0:10:23.07,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I mean, look at this guy, he's wearing stockings!
Dialogue: 2,0:10:23.07,0:10:23.85,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,戴假发
Dialogue: 1,0:10:23.07,0:10:23.85,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,A wig!
Dialogue: 2,0:10:23.85,0:10:25.00,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,还化妆
Dialogue: 1,0:10:23.85,0:10:25.00,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Makeup!
Dialogue: 2,0:10:25.00,0:10:26.73,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他还骑马
Dialogue: 1,0:10:25.00,0:10:26.73,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,He rides horses!
Dialogue: 2,0:10:26.73,0:10:28.21,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,给里给气
Dialogue: 1,0:10:26.73,0:10:28.21,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Gayiiiii!
Dialogue: 2,0:10:28.21,0:10:33.25,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不可避免地，到了2040年，理查德大叔也会在圣诞晚宴上扫兴地说
Dialogue: 1,0:10:28.21,0:10:33.25,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Inevitably, Uncle Richard will ruin Christmas dinner in the twenty-forties by saying,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:33.25,0:10:35.69,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,2010年代的生活可比现在好太多了
Dialogue: 1,0:10:33.25,0:10:35.69,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Life was so much better in the twenty-tens,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:35.69,0:10:39.76,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们必须回归传统，那时候，婚姻是缔结在两个人类之间的
Dialogue: 1,0:10:35.69,0:10:39.76,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,We must return to tradition when marriage was between two humans,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:39.76,0:10:43.71,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而不是像现在这些“机器人性恋”，毒害我们的孩子
Dialogue: 1,0:10:39.76,0:10:43.71,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,not these robo-sexuals indoctrinating our kids.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:43.99,0:10:51.52,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们现在都清楚，尽管有各种缺陷，现代生活还是优于以往任何时代
Dialogue: 1,0:10:43.99,0:10:51.52,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,We all know by now that despite its flaws, modern life is superior to anything that came before, in nearly any single way.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:51.52,0:10:57.75,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,既然如此，为什么我们有成千上万的老登在歌颂老黄油刀
Dialogue: 1,0:10:51.52,0:10:57.75,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,In that case, why do we have literally thousands of old people celebrating old butter knives, 
Dialogue: 2,0:10:57.75,0:11:04.07,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,更有无数的年轻人在抱怨机械化农业呢，我想我找到答案了
Dialogue: 1,0:10:57.75,0:11:04.07,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and even more young people complaining about mechanised agriculture? I think I know why.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:04.07,0:11:07.42,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,两德在34年前重新统一
Dialogue: 1,0:11:04.07,0:11:07.42,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The two Germanys reunited 34 years ago, 
Dialogue: 2,0:11:07.42,0:11:13.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但那些曾在东德生活过的人，仍未放弃对旧共产主义制度的怀念
Dialogue: 1,0:11:07.42,0:11:13.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,but those who lived in East Germany still haven't given up their nostalgia for the old communist system.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:13.12,0:11:16.45,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,大多数东德人同意这个说法：
Dialogue: 1,0:11:13.12,0:11:16.45,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,A majority of East Germans agree with the statement, 
Dialogue: 2,0:11:16.45,0:11:22.48,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,东德的好处多于坏处，虽然有些问题，但那里的生活挺好
Dialogue: 1,0:11:16.45,0:11:22.48,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,East Germany had more good sides than bad sides, there were some problems, but life was good there.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:22.48,0:11:28.47,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然而与此同时，83%的东德人赞成向市场经济过渡
Dialogue: 1,0:11:22.48,0:11:28.47,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Yet at the same time, 83% of East Germans approved the transition to a market economy,
Dialogue: 2,0:11:28.47,0:11:31.68,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,并且，从1990年到2019年，表示对生活“满意”的东德人数量
Dialogue: 1,0:11:28.47,0:11:31.68,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and the number of East Germans saying they are satisfied with their life 
Dialogue: 2,0:11:31.68,0:11:36.59,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,激增了44个百分点
Dialogue: 1,0:11:31.68,0:11:36.59,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,increased by 44 percentage points from 1990 to 2019.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:36.59,0:11:37.55,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这又是怎么一回事呢？
Dialogue: 1,0:11:36.59,0:11:37.55,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,What gives?
Dialogue: 2,0:11:37.55,0:11:41.36,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,嗯，当被问及他们具体怀念东德的什么时
Dialogue: 1,0:11:37.55,0:11:41.36,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Well, when asked what they specifically missed about East Germany, 
Dialogue: 2,0:11:41.36,0:11:44.90,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,很少有受访者真正提到经济体制
Dialogue: 1,0:11:41.36,0:11:44.90,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,very few respondents actually said the economic system,
Dialogue: 2,0:11:44.90,0:11:46.27,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,或是共产主义政府
Dialogue: 1,0:11:44.90,0:11:46.27,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the communist government, 
Dialogue: 2,0:11:46.27,0:11:51.38,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,或是那个把每个人都变成偏执狂、互相监视邻居的“斯塔西”
Dialogue: 1,0:11:46.27,0:11:51.38,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,or the Stasi turning everyone into paranoid freaks spying on their neighbours.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:51.38,0:11:56.59,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们最怀念的，是那时的学校系统、独特的食物、公共艺术
Dialogue: 1,0:11:51.38,0:11:56.59,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,What they missed the most was the school system, the unique food, the public art,
Dialogue: 2,0:11:56.59,0:11:59.85,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,以及那种“大家都在为共同目标而奋斗”的感觉
Dialogue: 1,0:11:56.59,0:11:59.85,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the idea that they were all working towards a common goal, 
Dialogue: 2,0:11:59.85,0:12:03.53,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,即便那个目标实际上遥不可及
Dialogue: 1,0:11:59.85,0:12:03.53,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,even if that goal wasn't actually getting any closer.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:03.78,0:12:07.07,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们怀念的是那时一切的“简单纯粹”
Dialogue: 1,0:12:03.78,0:12:07.07,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They miss how simpler everything was back then.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:07.07,0:12:10.27,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,东德人享受着过去的美学
Dialogue: 1,0:12:07.07,0:12:10.27,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,East Germans enjoy the aesthetics of the past, 
Dialogue: 2,0:12:10.27,0:12:14.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但他们中的大多数都承认，今天的生活更美好
Dialogue: 1,0:12:10.27,0:12:14.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,but most of them recognise their lives are better today.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:14.12,0:12:20.96,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我想，这正是这种心态的核心，无论是要求恢复包办婚姻的极端保守派
Dialogue: 1,0:12:14.12,0:12:20.96,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I think that's at the core of this mindset, from the hyper-conservatives demanding a return to arranged marriages,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:20.96,0:12:24.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,还是你家在Facebook上转发老式电话亭的奶奶
Dialogue: 1,0:12:20.96,0:12:24.72,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,to your grandma sharing Facebook posts about phone boxes.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:24.72,0:12:29.48,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,都会感觉现代生活似乎有点“素”，甚至可以说，有些寡淡无味
Dialogue: 1,0:12:24.72,0:12:29.48,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,modern life can seem a little vegetarian, somewhat bland.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:29.48,0:12:33.28,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,从建筑到邮筒，一切都被简化了
Dialogue: 1,0:12:29.48,0:12:33.28,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Everything from buildings to post boxes have been simplified,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:33.28,0:12:37.75,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,从日常生活的斑斓画卷中，抹去了一些丰富的色彩
Dialogue: 1,0:12:33.28,0:12:37.75,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,removing some of the richness from the tapestry of everyday life.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:37.75,0:12:42.71,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当一切都可以在线购买，所有人动动手指就能联系到
Dialogue: 1,0:12:37.75,0:12:42.71,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,When everything can be bought online, and everyone can be contacted at an arm's reach,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:42.71,0:12:45.81,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,你还有什么理由非得跑去酒吧社交
Dialogue: 1,0:12:42.71,0:12:45.81,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,what reason do you have to go to socialise at the pub, 
Dialogue: 2,0:12:45.81,0:12:50.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,跟蔬果店老板唠嗑，或者干脆出门呢
Dialogue: 1,0:12:45.81,0:12:50.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,gossip with the greengrocer, or go outside at all?
Dialogue: 2,0:12:50.12,0:12:54.02,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当在线追剧刷视频就能取代所有其他爱好时
Dialogue: 1,0:12:50.12,0:12:54.02,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,When consuming media online can replace all other hobbies,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:54.02,0:12:58.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,你还有什么理由去发展成一个“有趣”的人呢
Dialogue: 1,0:12:54.02,0:12:58.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,what reason do you have to develop into an interesting person?
Dialogue: 2,0:12:58.44,0:13:01.91,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,自然而然，这让人们变得非常孤单，也非常怨愤
Dialogue: 1,0:12:58.44,0:13:01.91,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Naturally, this makes people very lonely and very bitter.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:01.91,0:13:07.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,回望过去，便很容易认为，逝去时光里的人们更快乐、更会社交
Dialogue: 1,0:13:01.91,0:13:07.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It's easy to look back and think people were happier and more sociable in days gone by.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:07.38,0:13:10.80,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,如何扭转这一切，超出了本视频的讨论范围
Dialogue: 1,0:13:07.38,0:13:10.80,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,How we can undo this is beyond the scope of this video,
Dialogue: 2,0:13:10.80,0:13:15.05,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,所以，我将留给你们一段摘自日本古籍《叶隐》的文字
Dialogue: 1,0:13:10.80,0:13:15.05,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,so I'll leave you with an extract from the Japanese book Hagakure.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:15.05,0:13:19.46,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,故事讲述了一位诞生于和平年代的年轻武士
Dialogue: 1,0:13:15.05,0:13:19.46,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The narrative follows a young warrior born into an era of peace,
Dialogue: 2,0:13:19.46,0:13:23.28,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在武士间最后的大战结束几十年后才出生
Dialogue: 1,0:13:19.46,0:13:23.28,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,born decades after the last great wars between the samurai.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:23.58,0:13:30.98,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他被无聊所困，渴望冲突重现，只为给自己的生命赋予意义
Dialogue: 1,0:13:23.58,0:13:30.98,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Plagued by boredom, he yearns for a return to conflict, solely to provide purpose in his life.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:30.98,0:13:36.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,时代之风渐渐地滑向低俗
Dialogue: 1,0:13:30.98,0:13:36.92,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It is said that what is called the spirit of an age is something to which one cannot return.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.98,0:13:36.92,Yahei-1920x1080,atg3,0,0,0,,译本来源：广西师范大学出版社《叶隐闻书》
Dialogue: 2,0:13:36.92,0:13:41.35,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,是末世来临的证据
Dialogue: 1,0:13:36.92,0:13:41.35,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,That this spirit gradually dissipates is due to the world's coming to an end.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:41.35,0:13:47.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,想把当代恢复到百年前的良好风俗
Dialogue: 1,0:13:41.35,0:13:47.60,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,For this reason, although one would like to change today's world back to the spirit of 100 years or more ago,
Dialogue: 2,0:13:47.60,0:13:49.33,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,是不可能的
Dialogue: 1,0:13:47.60,0:13:49.33,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,it cannot be done.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:49.33,0:13:54.76,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在哪个时代就做好哪个时代的事，这才是最重要的
Dialogue: 1,0:13:49.33,0:13:54.76,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Therefore, it is important to make the best out of every generation.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:57.20,0:14:01.55,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪就算大雨滂沱又何妨♪{\i}
Dialogue: 1,0:13:57.20,0:14:01.55,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,What does it matter if rain comes your way?
Dialogue: 2,0:14:01.85,0:14:04.96,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪就算雨滴终日敲打♪{\i}
Dialogue: 1,0:14:01.85,0:14:04.96,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And raindrops pattern all day?
Dialogue: 2,0:14:05.42,0:14:09.76,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪倾盆大雨也不该让你忧郁♪{\i}
Dialogue: 1,0:14:05.42,0:14:09.76,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The rain descending should not make you blue.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:10.19,0:14:15.29,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪美好的结局正在前方等你♪{\i}
Dialogue: 1,0:14:10.19,0:14:15.29,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The happy ending is waiting for you.